article.headline: Arkansas State 64, Liberty 63
article.story: LYNCHBURG, Va. (AP) -- Tevoris Thompson came off the bench to score 24 points, and Dewarick Spencer added 15 and 10 rebounds as Arkansas State beat Liberty 64-63 Monday. Thompson connected on six 3-pointers, including one with three seconds remaining to erase a two-point deficit for the Indians. The lead changed hands 10 times, with neither team gaining more than a a seven-point advantage. The score was tied 30-30 at halftime. Arkansas State led 60-53 with 4:27 left in the game, but the Flames scored nine of the next 10 points and regained the lead with 55 seconds left on a jumper by Jason Sarchet. Sarchet led the Flames with 16 points, and Gabe Martin added 12.
